# PROJECT_STATUS Update Rule

Any meaningful repo change must include a `PROJECT_STATUS.md` update in the same work:

- Update status for shipped features, in-progress work, blockers, env/infra changes, and next milestones.
- Update "Last updated" and keep sections current (built, in progress, planned, stack, environment).
- If branch/deploy/domain/monitoring changes, reflect them in `PROJECT_STATUS.md`.
- If a change affects cross-repo management reporting, note it for `knowledge/zyntel-playbook/06-operations/projects-status.md`.

Do not consider implementation complete until `PROJECT_STATUS.md` is aligned.

